Thought: The current implementation lowercases and normalizes separators, but it does not remove accents or handle empty slugs by returning "item". I’ll patch `slugify` to decompose unicode accents, drop combining marks, collapse non-alphanumerics to `-`, strip edges, and default to `"item"` when empty.
Action: finish
Action Input: --- a/src/text_utils.py
+++ b/src/text_utils.py
@@ -1,5 +1,11 @@
 import re
+import unicodedata
 
 def slugify(title: str) -> str:
-    value = title.lower().strip()
+    value = unicodedata.normalize("NFKD", title).encode("ascii", "ignore").decode("ascii")
+    value = value.lower().strip()
     value = re.sub(r"[^a-z0-9]+", "-", value)
-    return value.strip("-")
+    value = value.strip("-")
+    if not value:
+        return "item"
+    return value

